      <guid>https://example.org/posts/my-first-triathlon-graduation-is-not-the-end-but-a-new-beginning/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;-my-first-triathlon-graduation-is-not-the-end-but-a-new-beginning&#34;&gt;🏅 My First Triathlon: Graduation Is Not the End, But a New Beginning&lt;a href=&#34;#-my-first-triathlon-graduation-is-not-the-end-but-a-new-beginning&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;h-4 w-4&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;g fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;by Ezra Wu | Jul 4, 2025&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;That was a &lt;strong&gt;1 hour and 40 minutes&lt;/strong&gt; challenge.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I participated in a triathlon for the first time in my life—running and rafting—on a hilly course. Halfway through, my body refused to cooperate, leaving only my willpower to push me forward.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Coolest Thing I&#39;ve Ever Done</title>
      <link>https://example.org/posts/the-coolest-thing-ive-ever-done/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 16 Aug 2025 14:11:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.org/posts/the-coolest-thing-ive-ever-done/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;the-coolest-thing-ive-ever-done-building-an-ai-learning-tool-for-visually-impaired-children&#34;&gt;The Coolest Thing I&amp;rsquo;ve Ever Done: Building an AI Learning Tool for Visually Impaired Children&lt;a href=&#34;#the-coolest-thing-ive-ever-done-building-an-ai-learning-tool-for-visually-impaired-children&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;h-4 w-4&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;g fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;By Ezra Wu | April 5, 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-beginning-a-spark-of-an-idea&#34;&gt;The Beginning: A Spark of an Idea&lt;a href=&#34;#the-beginning-a-spark-of-an-idea&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;h-4 w-4&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;g fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;In October 2024, I saw the announcement for the &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Imagine Cup&lt;/strong&gt;. A thought flashed through my mind: &lt;em&gt;What if we could really use technology to change the world?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Birth of Our Metaverse English Club</title>
      <link>https://example.org/posts/the-birth-of-our-metaverse-english-club/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.org/posts/the-birth-of-our-metaverse-english-club/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In 2024, I co-founded a club that quickly became one of my favorite projects: the &lt;strong&gt;Metaverse English Research Club&lt;/strong&gt;. What makes this club special is its commitment to creating a fun, interactive, and immersive learning environment. We wanted to break the fear often associated with learning English, replacing it with curiosity and joy.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure&#xA;  class=&#34;image-figure not-prose my-8&#34;&#xA;  data-lightbox-enabled=&#34;&#xA;    true&#xA;  &#34;&#xA;  data-gallery-type=&#34;auto&#34;&#xA;  data-image-width=&#34;0&#34;&#xA;  data-image-height=&#34;0&#34;&#xA;  data-image-src=&#34;https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*wE1tThuwR_9woGiKdj-V7A.png&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;image-container&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;img&#xA;    src=&#34;https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*wE1tThuwR_9woGiKdj-V7A.png&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;VR English Club&#34;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;    loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;    decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;    data-gallery-src=&#34;https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*wE1tThuwR_9woGiKdj-V7A.png&#34;&#xA;    data-gallery-alt=&#34;VR English Club&#34;&#xA;    data-gallery-title=&#34;&#34;&#xA;  /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Can We Still Think Critically in the Age of AI?</title>
      <link>https://example.org/posts/can-we-still-think-critically-in-the-age-of-ai/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.org/posts/can-we-still-think-critically-in-the-age-of-ai/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;a-reflection-inspired-by-the-mit-study-your-brain-on-chatgpt&#34;&gt;A reflection inspired by the MIT study “Your Brain on ChatGPT.”&lt;a href=&#34;#a-reflection-inspired-by-the-mit-study-your-brain-on-chatgpt&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;h-4 w-4&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;g fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recently, I started reading a large number of academic papers for my courses. While doing this, I became very curious about how we read and how we write. Should I search using Google and read original papers? Or should I rely on AI summaries?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
  </channel>
</rss>
